quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  17,85,"They will ask you about the Ruh. Say: ´The Ruh is my Lord´s concern. You have only been given a little knowledge.´"
  17,86,If We wished We could take away what We have revealed to you and then you would not find any to guard you from Us —
  17,87,but for a mercy from your Lord. His favour to you is indeed immense
  17,88,"Say: ´If both men and jinn banded together to produce the like of this Qur´an, they could never produce anything like it, even if they backed each other up.´"
  17,89,"We have variegated throughout this Qur´an all kinds of examples for people, but most people spurn anything but kufr"
  17,90,"They say, ´We will not believe you until you make a spring gush out from the earth for us"
  17,91,or have a garden of dates and grapes which you make rivers come pouring through
  17,92,"or make the sky, as you claim, fall down on us in lumps; or bring Allah and the angels here as a guarantee"
  17,93,"or possess a house built out of gleaming gold; or ascend up into heaven — and even then we will not believe in your ascent unless you bring us down a book to read!´ Say: ´Glory be to my Lord! Am I anything but a human messenger?´"